More tactics that are not used, found using the linter at #11308.

The PR consists of tactic removals, whitespace changes and replacing a porting note by an explanation.

  * [Lint style](https://github.com/leanprover-community/mathlib4/actions/runs/8283944952/job/22668342689)

Maybe you also need a "single tactic `first`" linter
```suggestion
  | 0 => by constructor <;> exact elim0
```
As before, I'm not sure you should be touching this if you're not solving the porting note

I think that the porting note is simply pointing out that a `,` does not stop the `cases` pattern.  This is the [Zulip thread](https://leanprover.zulipchat.com/#narrow/stream/270676-lean4/topic/error.20puzzle/near/426043583).  So, I am going to remove the porting note!
